#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn50.99-108"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 50 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 50 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:0.2"
msgid "9. Punaoghavagga "
msgstr "9. Another Chapter on Floods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:0.3"
msgid "99–108. Punaoghādisutta "
msgstr "99–108. Another Series on Floods, Etc. "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.253, sc1
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.3"
msgid "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ avijjā—"
msgstr "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.4"
msgid "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. "
msgstr "These are the five higher fetters. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.5"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya pañca balāni bhāvetabbāni. "
msgstr "The five powers should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "

msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.6"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.7"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhābalaṃ bhāveti … pe … paññābalaṃ bhāveti rāgavinayapariyosānaṃ dosavinayapariyosānaṃ mohavinayapariyosānaṃ. "
msgstr "A mendicant develops the powers of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom, which culminate in the removal of greed, hate, and delusion. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.8"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya imāni pañca balāni bhāvetabbānī”ti. "
msgstr "These five powers should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr "(To be expanded as in SN 45.171–179, with the above as the final discourse.) "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:1.10"
msgid "Oghavaggo dasamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:2.1"
msgid "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, "
msgstr "Floods, bonds, grasping, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:2.2"
msgid "ganthā anusayena ca; "
msgstr "ties, and underlying tendencies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:2.3"
msgid "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, "
msgstr "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:2.4"
msgid "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. "
msgstr "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn50.99-108:2.5"
msgid "Balasaṃyuttaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the Powers is the sixth section."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
